          Versions follow SemVer. Breaking changes are flagged in Deprecated and Removed sections. Latest v2.4.1 Released Aug 12, 2024 LTS Track v2.2.x EOL v1.x  Dec 2024 v 2.4.1 Released August 12, 2024 stable Added New ferroflux::stream::Backpressure policy with adaptive window sizing for embedded targets. Configuration DSL now supports inline @import directives for sharing broker profiles across deployments. Gateway endpoint POST /v1/devices/:id/heartbeat for low-power keepalive on cellular links. Rust SDK: async fn Device::flush_with_timeout(...) returning structured FlushReport . Changed Default MQTT QoS lowered from 2 to 1 for new device registrations. Existing devices unaffected. TLS handshake timeout raised to 12s to accommodate constrained NB-IoT modems. CLI fluxctl now prints color-coded severity in --watch mode. Fixed Race condition when a stream is closed during tick() on single-threaded async executors. Incorrect schema fingerprint for nested Map<String, Bytes> fields. Panic in RetentionPolicy::compact() when storage backend reports a future timestamp. Deprecated DEPRECATED Device::push_raw(&[u8]) — use Device::push<T: Encode>(value) . Removal planned for v2.6. DEPRECATED Endpoint GET /v1/alerts/by-tag — superseded by query parameter ?tag= on /v1/alerts . v 2.3.0 Released May 28, 2024 stable Added WebSocket transport ( wss:// ) as a first-class alternative to MQTT for environments behind restrictive proxies. Configuration key broker.fallback_endpoints accepting an ordered list of failover URLs. Alert::correlation_id field, propagated through downstream webhooks. flux # Excerpt: new fallback configuration broker "north-eu" {
  endpoint          = "mqtts://north-eu.ferroflux.io:8883" fallback_endpoints = [ "mqtts://north-eu-backup.ferroflux.io:8883" , "wss://relay.ferroflux.io:443/mqtt" ,
  ]
  reconnect_after   = 5s } Changed Telemetry batch size raised from 32 to 64 by default; tunable via stream.batch_size . The fluxctl deploy command now requires explicit --profile when multiple profiles are detected. Fixed Memory leak in long-lived StreamSubscriber when consumer drops mid-batch. Schema migration silently dropped Option<T> fields with default None . JWT validation rejected tokens issued exactly at the nbf boundary. Deprecated DEPRECATED Environment variable FFX_LEGACY_AUTH=1 — basic auth fallback will be removed in v3.0. v 2.2.4 Released February 14, 2024 LTS Added Long-Term Support designation — v2.2.x receives security patches through Q4 2025. Hardware-attested device identities on supported MCUs (ESP32-S3, STM32H7, nRF9160). Prometheus exporter on port 9477 exposing 28 gateway-internal metrics. New retention strategy tiered_cold for cost-tiered S3-compatible storage. Changed Default log format switched from text to JSON; revert with logging.format = "text" . SDK MSRV bumped to Rust 1.74 . Security CVE-2024-2114 — patched a denial-of-service vector in the schema parser when handling deeply nested types. Severity: Medium . Fixed Reconnect storm when broker certificate rotated mid-session. Off-by-one in batch ordering under specific clock-skew conditions. v 2.1.0 Released November 3, 2023 stable Added Alert routing rules with declarative match blocks in .flux . no_std feature flag for the SDK — verified on Cortex-M4F targets. Per-stream encryption-at-rest keys. Changed Auth token TTL default reduced from 24h to 6h ; refresh tokens unchanged. Fixed Spurious ErrSchemaMismatch when a non-required field is added in a minor schema bump. Gateway returned 500 instead of 413 for oversized payloads. Deprecated DEPRECATED stream.legacy_framing — the v1 framing protocol will be removed in v2.5. v 2.0.0 Released July 18, 2023 major FerroFlux 2.0 is a full rewrite of the gateway and SDK in async Rust. The v1.x C/C++ daemon is retained
              only as a compatibility shim and is scheduled for end-of-life in December 2024. Added Brand-new Rust SDK with async/await, zero-copy serialization via rkyv , and structured errors. Declarative .flux configuration DSL replacing the verbose INI files of v1.x. Multi-tenant project isolation at the gateway level. Native OpenTelemetry traces emitted from all SDK call sites. Changed Wire protocol now uses CBOR + Zstd framing. Legacy framing remains available behind a feature flag. Authentication switched to OAuth 2.1 with PKCE for interactive clients and mutual TLS for devices. Removed The ferroflux-c static library — superseded by the Rust SDK's C FFI bindings. The HTTP/1.0-only fallback transport. Deprecated DEPRECATED The entire v1.x configuration format. A migration tool ships as fluxctl migrate-v1 . v 1.x series Mar 2021 — Apr 2023 EOL Dec 2024 Show legacy releases (v1.0 → v1.7) 8 releases · archived v1.7.2 April 4, 2023 Final v1.x feature release. Backports continue until EOL. Added --export-csv flag to ferroflux-cli stream . v1.6.0 November 11, 2022 Introduced experimental Rust bindings under ferroflux-rs (now superseded by the official SDK). TLS 1.3 support on Linux daemon builds. v1.5.0 May 22, 2022 Added cluster-mode broker peering across three regions. DEPRECATED XML output format for devices export . v1.4.1 January 30, 2022 Patched memory corruption in payload decoder (CVE-2022-0118). v1.3.0 September 9, 2021 First release with Windows daemon support. Added retention rules with day-bucket granularity. v1.2.0 June 14, 2021 Schema registry endpoint added at /v0/schemas . v1.1.0 April 28, 2021 Added rate-limit headers on all gateway responses. v1.0.0 March 2, 2021 Initial public release of FerroFlux Systems middleware. © 2024 FerroFlux Systems · Documentation built from docs@a2f91e0 Edit this page Report an issue RSS On this page v2.4.1 — Aug 2024 v2.3.0 — May 2024 v2.2.4 — Feb 2024 (LTS) v2.1.0 — Nov 2023 v2.0.0 — Jul 2023 v1.x legacy series Subscribe to releases New versions are published the second Monday of each month. Security patches ship out-of-band.
